  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the wood fired oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the yogurt, sugar, and eggs until smooth.",
    "Add the mung bean paste, coconut milk, and red bean paste to the bowl and mix until well combined.",
    "Stir in the green tea extract and wood fired sea salt.",
    "Pour the mixture into 4 small ramekins or cups.",
    "Place the ramekins in the wood fired oven and bake for 20 minutes.",
    "Remove the ramekins from the oven and let them cool for 5 minutes.",
    "Serve the Che Ba Mau warm, with a molten center and a crispy exterior."
